Global Merchant Services (GMS) is Accounts Payable system which takes care of Merchants affiliation with American Express. It maintains financial 
and non-financial characteristics like name, address, bank details, Terms and Condition of Merchants with American Express. This system takes care of 
processing transactions submitted by merchants from US, CANADA, LAC (Latin American countries), EMEA (Europe and Middle East Asia) and APAC
(Japan Asia-Pacific and Australia) markets to American Express for their card member spending. It does validation, risk validation and pricing of 
transactions as per Term and Condition between American Express and merchant and make the payment to the merchants for their submissions. This system 
also creates different types business reports and different types of merchant statements. This system also sends financial and non-financial data to various 
interfacing system as Card Member system for Authorization and Business reporting system for doing deep data analysis for driving business decision on it.


